<br>
The best explanation I have read for this lies in the nature of bolts and arrows. A bolt is apparently a short-lived NPC that simply tracks the target and runs collision detection. If it hits the target, boom, run DD functions as normal and the bolt is dead. If its hits anything else, it does no damage if it is an object or a PC, it hurts the mis-targetted NPC if its a mob (I've broken mezzes like this with BWS. Not cool).<br>
<br>
So anyway, we come back to the focus items. It is suspected that focus item code performs a check to see if the spell is being activated by a right click item, and does not apply damage if this is the case. The bolt however is identical to the one created by a true <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Cinder Bolt</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> spell, and so when the damage is checked there is no way for the focus code to determine how the bolt was fired - and so unless you reclick your staff very quickly (and hence there is a clicky item currently active) the server simply assumes that the bolt is a true nuke, not a right-click.<br>
<br>
